EU Referendum: Is this the worst spelling error ever?

2016-06-22

  SWNS

The notice, made on a piece of cardboard, was spotted tied to a set of railings beside a roundabout in Chelmsford, Essex.

It reads "Invest in Britan not Brussels" but contains a rather comical typo.

And it has sent social media crazy today.

Vee Harvey wrote: "Shows the intelligence in the Brexit camp!"

And Robert Hastings added: "The Only Way is Essex, the Only Way is Out."

Others called for more money to be spent on education in the UK.

Jon Pearce posted: "Maybe more money should be used for schools."

While Maxine Gibson shared: "A good example of why I'm voting inâ€¦."

The UK decides tomorrow whether it stays or leaves the EU.

